The paper presents a novel neural network architecture that learns to form propositional representations with an explicitly relational structure from raw pixel data. This involves tasks related to visual reasoning, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The architecture is also pre-trained on a curriculum of tasks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the workings of the trained model, which involves understanding the behavior of neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), making it likely to fall under these five categories.
